data.content:
Here are the better MSTest assertions for each case:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetActiveUsers_ReturnsOnlyActiveUsers()
{
    var service = new UserService();
    var users = service.GetActiveUsers();

    // Instead of Assert.IsTrue(users.Count > 0)
    Assert.AreNotEqual(0, users.Count);

    // Instead of Assert.IsTrue(users.All(u => u.IsActive))
    CollectionAssert.AllItemsAreNotNull(users);
    foreach (var user in users)
        Assert.IsTrue(user.IsActive, $"User {user.Name} is not active");

    // Instead of Assert.IsTrue(users.Count() == 3)
    Assert.AreEqual(3, users.Count);

    // Instead of Assert.IsTrue(admin != null)
    var admin = users.Single(u => u.Role == "Admin");
    Assert.IsNotNull(admin);
}
```

**Key improvements:**

| Instead of | Use | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `Assert.IsTrue(x > 0)` | `Assert.AreNotEqual(0, x)` | Shows expected vs actual on failure |
| `Assert.IsTrue(count == 3)` | `Assert.AreEqual(3, count)` | Failure message shows "Expected: 3, Actual: 5" |
| `Assert.IsTrue(x != null)` | `Assert.IsNotNull(x)` | Clearer intent and failure message |

**Other useful `CollectionAssert` methods:**
- `CollectionAssert.Contains(collection, item)`
- `CollectionAssert.AllItemsAreUnique(collection)`
- `CollectionAssert.AreEquivalent(expected, actual)` — same items, any order
- `CollectionAssert.IsSubsetOf(subset, superset)`

The main benefit: when tests fail, you get diagnostic messages like `"Expected: 3, Actual: 1"` instead of just `"Assert.IsTrue failed"`.
